erts until about  445 , when he established his archiepiscopal see at Armagh. By the time of his death almost the whole of Ireland is said to have been converted to Christianity. He is also credited with codifying the laws of Ireland. In his Latin autobiography, as well as in later tradition, his name appears as <i>Patricius</i> ‘patrician’ (i.e. belonging to the Roman senatorial or noble class), but this may actually represent a Latinized form of some lost Celtic (British) name. In Ireland in particular, it has been one of the most enduringly popular boys' names."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Patrick DeHome was born in 1170, in Home, Berwickshire, Scotland, his father, Patrick Hume I, was 30 and his mother, Cecilia de Fraser, was 20. He married spouse Patrick DeHome before 1190, in Europe. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1248, in his hometown, at the age of 78."},"et":{"1170–1248":"1170–1248","–Female":"Surnud","1190–1266":"1190–1266","1140–Male":"1140–Surnud","1150–Female":"1150–Surnud","1190":"1190","1248":"1248","1266":"1266","1140":"1140","1150":"1150","1170":"1170","before 1190":"enne 1190","Europe":"Europe","Home, Berwickshire, Scotland":"Home, Berwickshire, Scotland"},"fi":{"1170–1248":"1170–1248","–Female":"Kuollut","1190–1266":"1190–1266","1140–Male":"1140–Kuollut","1150–Female":"1150–Kuollut","1190":"1190","1248":"1248","1266":"1266","1140":"1140","1150":"1150","1170":"1170","before 1190":"ennen vuotta 1190","Europe":"Europe","Home, Berwickshire, Scotland":"Home, Berwickshire, Scotland"},"fr":{"1170–1248":"1170–1248","–Female":"Décédée","1190–1266":"1190–1266","1140–Male":"1140–Décédé","1150–Female":"1150–Décédée","1190":"1190","1248":"1248","1266":"1266","1140":"1140","1150":"1150","1170":"1170","before 1190":"avant 1190","Europe":"Europe","Home, Berwickshire, Scotland":"Home, Berwickshire, Écosse","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Patrick DeHome est né en 1170, à Home, Berwickshire, Écosse, son père, Patrick Hume I, avait 30 ans et sa m